So the changelog entry we get in atlassian-connect webhooks from JIRA are quite confusing when it comes to figuring out which field changed.

So far from what I can tell, 'field' will be this:
* For all system fields it's the id of the system field (e.g. 'summary', 'description', etc)
** EXCEPT fixVersion, version & issuelinks.  For those it's 'Fix Version', 'Version', 'Link'
* For custom fields, you get the field name not the field id (so 'My text field' instead of 'customfield_11212')

So we can kinda do a lookup from field Id -> field name and try both to see if there's something in the changelog, but Fix Version seems completely hard coded.  /rest/api/2/field returns id of 'fixVersions' and name of 'Fix Version/s'.  The changelog contains neither so we have to hard-code this lookup!

Her's an example with Fix Version:
{noformat}
"changelog": {
    "id": "17415",
    "items": [
      {
        "field": "Fix Version",
        "fieldtype": "jira",
        "from": null,
        "fromString": null,
        "to": "10001",
        "toString": "2"
      }
]}
{noformat}

Would be awesome if the changelog items could contain a 'fieldId' entry that's *always*  the fieldId!  Sure they can disappear for custom_fields, but we can just fall back to 'field' in that case.

